quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  18,106,""
  18,107,""
  18,108,""
  19,67,"Does not man remember that We created him before, while he was nothing?"
  19,68,"So by your Lord, surely, We shall gather them together, and (also) the Shayâtîn (devils) (with them), then We shall bring them round Hell on their knees."
  19,69,"Then indeed We shall drag out from every sect all those who were worst in obstinate rebellion against the Most Gracious (Allâh)."
  20,49,"Fir‘aun (Pharaoh) said: "
  20,50,"[Mûsâ (Moses)] said: "
  20,51,"[Fir‘aun (Pharaoh)] said: "
  21,25,"And We did not send any Messenger before you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) but We revealed to him (saying): Lâ ilâha illa Ana [none has the right to be worshipped but I (Allâh)], so worship Me (Alone and none else)."
  21,26,"And they say: "
  21,27,"They speak not until He has spoken, and they act on His Command."
  22,1,"O mankind! Fear your Lord and be dutiful to Him! Verily, the earthquake of the Hour (of Judgement) is a terrible thing."
  22,2,"The Day you shall see it, every nursing mother will forget her nursling, and every pregnant one will drop her load, and you shall see mankind as in a drunken state, yet they will not be drunken, but severe will be the Torment of Allâh."
  22,3,"And among mankind is he who disputes concerning Allâh, without knowledge, and follows every rebellious (disobedient to Allâh) Shaitân (devil) (devoid of every kind of good)."